 **PRIVACY POLICY — S1BOX CLOUD**

(Last Updated: November 27, 2025)

---

## 1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how **Synth1ca** (“we”, “us”, “our”) collects, uses, and protects information related to the **S1Box Cloud** platform.

We follow U.S. (including CCPA-compatible disclosures) and Canadian (PIPEDA) privacy standards.

We practice **data minimization**.

---

## 2. Information We Collect

### 2.1 Email Address

Collected during Stripe checkout.  
Used for:

- Subscription management
    
- Dashboard token delivery
    
- Support communication
    

We do NOT send marketing emails unless the user opts in.

### 2.2 Authentication Tokens

- Tokens are generated for dashboard access
    
- Stored **hashed** (SHA256)
    
- Never stored in plaintext
    
- Expire after 90 days
    

### 2.3 Honeypot Attack Logs

These are technical logs from attacker interactions:

- Attacker IP
    
- Timestamp
    
- Event message
    
- Raw log lines
    
- Attempted username/password (if applicable)
    
- Command attempts (if applicable)
    
- Port, protocol, trap type
    

These logs are your data.

### 2.4 Enrichment Data (Pro Plan Only)

Includes:

- GeoIP
    
- Threat score
    
- TOR exit node status
    
- Spamhaus listing
    
- CISA KEV match
    
- Risk/confidence levels
    

These require sending attacker IPs to third-party providers.

### 2.5 Operational & System Data

We collect operational telemetry:

- Hub/server heartbeat
    
- CPU/memory usage
    
- Error logs
    
- Provisioning job events
    

This is required to maintain the platform.

---

## 3. What We Do NOT Collect

- Personal names
    
- User physical addresses
    
- Payment card data
    
- Billing addresses
    
- Passwords
    
- User browsing data
    
- User IP addresses (except security logging if aggressive rate abuse occurs)
    

Payment data is handled entirely by **Stripe**.

---

## 4. How We Use Data

We use data strictly to:

- Provide and maintain the S1Box Service
    
- Provision honeypots
    
- Display logs in the dashboard
    
- Enrich data (Pro plan)
    
- Improve platform stability
    
- Communicate with users (operational messages only)
    
- Maintain security
    

We do NOT:

- Sell user data
    
- Share user data for advertising
    
- Build user profiles
    
- Track users across websites
    

---

## 5. Data Sharing

We only share data with:

- Stripe (your email during checkout)
    
- Threat intelligence providers (attacker IPs for enrichment)
    
- Hosting providers (to run S1Box infrastructure)
    
- Law enforcement if legally required
    
- Contractors under NDA who maintain infrastructure (rare)
    

We never sell data.

---

## 6. Data Retention

- Basic: logs retained **30 days**
    
- Pro: logs retained **90 days**
    
- After cancellation: same retention applies
    
- After retention expires: permanent deletion
    

Email and subscription metadata may be retained for legal/accounting compliance.

---

## 7. Data Security

We follow industry best practices:

- TLS/HTTPS everywhere
    
- Token hashing (SHA256)
    
- Firewalling
    
- Access control and audit logs
    
- Encrypted database (if enabled in deployment)
    
- Least privilege access for internal systems
    
- Isolation between traps and core infrastructure
    

No system is perfectly secure, but we take reasonable technical and organizational measures.

---

## 8. User Rights

Depending on your region (U.S. states, PIPEDA in Canada), you may:

- Access your data
    
- Request deletion
    
- Request correction
    
- Request export (if supported)
    
- Withdraw consent (if applicable)
    

Contact us at **[hello@synth1ca.eu](mailto:hello@synth1ca.eu)** for requests.

We may require proof you control the subscription email.

---

## 9. Children’s Privacy

S1Box Cloud is not intended for anyone under **18 years old**.

We do not knowingly collect data from minors.

---

## 10. International Transfers

Data may be processed in multiple countries (depending on hub locations and cloud providers).  
Your use of the Service constitutes consent to such transfers.

---

## 11. Data Breach Notification

If a data breach occurs:

- We will notify affected users
    
- We will notify authorities when required
    
- We will take corrective action to address the issue
    

---

## 12. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy.  
Material changes will be communicated via email or dashboard.

---

